Global Vaporized Hydrogen Peroxide Disinfection Systems for Medical Devices (VHP Disinfection Systems for Medical Devices) Market Insights
Vaporized Hydrogen Peroxide Disinfection Systems for Medical Devices (VHP Disinfection Systems for Medical Devices) Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.3 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.8% from 2024 to 2030.

Vaporized Hydrogen Peroxide Disinfection Systems for Medical Devices (VHP Disinfection Systems for Medical Devices) Market Overview
The global Vaporized Hydrogen Peroxide (VHP) disinfection systems market for medical devices has seen robust growth due to the increasing demand for effective sterilization methods in healthcare facilities. In 2024, the market was valued at approximately USD 1.8 billion and is expected to witness a compounded annual growth rate (CAGR) of 9.3% over the forecast period (2025-2030). This surge is driven by rising healthcare requirements, strict sterilization regulations, and advancements in infection control technologies. The medical device sterilization market is especially influenced by the growing adoption of minimally invasive surgical techniques and the necessity for effective sterilization of high-risk medical equipment.

